      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Accordingly bread and water\nforms the Thanksgiving fare at the\ndining room Of the Industrial\nWorkers today, while across the\nstreet, at the Ondawa Inn, a free\ndinner is being served to laboring\nmen who prefer full stomachs to a\nfight for principle.\n\n\nA bulletin board announcing the\nbread and water resolution was\nposted at the Stevens street en-\ntrance to the I. w. w. hall this\nmorning. Only two meals of the\nbread and water are served at that,\nthis regulation being in conformity\nwith that pursued in the city Jail.\n\n\nOne of the first visitors at the\nIndustrial headquarters this morn.\ning was Attorney Bruce Rogers,\nwho fell in line with the order and\nsaid the bread and water was good\nenough for him. Rogers ia one of\nthe associate counsel for the\nWorkers."
    }
  ]
